### 2. Event Producer

#### [NEW] [form-component-item-select-event-producer.ts](file:///Users/shilo/Work/Projects/redbox/redbox-portal/feature/typeahead-onitemselect/angular/projects/researchdatabox/form/src/app/form-state/events/form-component-item-select-event-producer.ts)

Extends [FormComponentEventBaseProducerConsumer](file:///Users/shilo/Work/Projects/redbox/redbox-portal/feature/typeahead-onitemselect/angular/projects/researchdatabox/form/src/app/form-state/events/form-component-base-event-producer-consumer.ts#36-148).

**Lifecycle safety**: Uses `toObservable(component.selectedItem, {injector})` from `@angular/core/rxjs-interop` with an **explicit injector** passed from [FormBaseWrapperComponent](file:///Users/shilo/Work/Projects/redbox/redbox-portal/feature/typeahead-onitemselect/angular/projects/researchdatabox/form/src/app/component/base-wrapper.component.ts#34-196). This avoids injection context issues in a non-component class and fits the existing subscription-based teardown.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Initial emission risk**: `toObservable` emits the current signal value on subscribe. Since `selectedItem` starts as `null`, this would publish a spurious clear event during [bind()](file:///Users/shilo/Work/Projects/redbox/redbox-portal/feature/typeahead-onitemselect/angular/projects/researchdatabox/form/src/app/form-state/events/form-component-base-event-producer-consumer.ts#52-53) and wipe sibling fields on form init. Mitigate with `pipe(skipWhile(v => v === null))` â€” this skips only the initial `null` and still passes through any non-null value even if it were the first emission.
>
> **Context**: in practice `selectedItem` is `null` at bind time, but `skipWhile` makes correctness independent of this â€” a pre-set non-null value would still be emitted.

**[bind()](file:///Users/shilo/Work/Projects/redbox/redbox-portal/feature/typeahead-onitemselect/angular/projects/researchdatabox/form/src/app/form-state/events/form-component-base-event-producer-consumer.ts#52-53)**:
- Check `component.selectedItem` exists. If absent â†’ return (safe no-op).
- Resolve `fieldId` from `options.definition?.lineagePaths?.angularComponentsJsonPointer`. If absent â†’ return.
- Subscribe to `toObservable(component.selectedItem, {injector: options.injector}).pipe(skipWhile(v => v === null))` â†’ `publishItemSelected()`.
- After the initial null is skipped, publishes both null (cleared) and non-null (selected) values.
- **Missing injector**: If `options.injector` is absent, log a debug message and return (no-op) rather than throwing.

**[destroy()](file:///Users/shilo/Work/Projects/redbox/redbox-portal/feature/typeahead-onitemselect/angular/projects/researchdatabox/form/src/app/form-state/events/form-component-change-event-producer.ts#73-80)**: Calls `super.destroy()` â€” clears subscriptions map.

