### 3. Event Consumer

#### [NEW] [form-component-item-select-event-consumer.ts](file:///Users/shilo/Work/Projects/redbox/redbox-portal/feature/typeahead-onitemselect/angular/projects/researchdatabox/form/src/app/form-state/events/form-component-item-select-event-consumer.ts)

Extends [FormComponentEventBaseConsumer](file:///Users/shilo/Work/Projects/redbox/redbox-portal/feature/typeahead-onitemselect/angular/projects/researchdatabox/form/src/app/form-state/events/form-component-base-event-consumer.ts#36-316) with `consumedEventType = 'field.item.selected'`.

**[bind()](file:///Users/shilo/Work/Projects/redbox/redbox-portal/feature/typeahead-onitemselect/angular/projects/researchdatabox/form/src/app/form-state/events/form-component-base-event-producer-consumer.ts#52-53)** â€” overrides base to skip expressions:
- Read `onItemSelect` from `options.definition?.compConfigJson?.component?.config`.
- If absent â†’ return.
- Resolve own JSON pointer from `options.definition?.lineagePaths?.angularComponentsJsonPointer`. **If absent â†’ return** (prevents cross-group leakage; no name-based fallback). Log a debug message so missing pointers are diagnosable during config errors.
- Resolve `control` from definition/component model.
- Subscribe to `field.item.selected` events, **filtering by sibling scope**: compare parent JSON pointer of event's `fieldId` with own parent pointer using a centralized `getParentPointer()` private helper. **Edge cases**: empty, root-only (`/`), or no-slash pointers â†’ skip (no match).
- On match â†’ call `handleItemSelected()` (not [consumeEvent()](file:///Users/shilo/Work/Projects/redbox/redbox-portal/feature/typeahead-onitemselect/angular/projects/researchdatabox/form/src/app/form-state/events/form-component-change-event-consumer.ts#19-50)).

**[consumeEvent(_event, _expression)](file:///Users/shilo/Work/Projects/redbox/redbox-portal/feature/typeahead-onitemselect/angular/projects/researchdatabox/form/src/app/form-state/events/form-component-change-event-consumer.ts#19-50)** â€” explicit no-op override with underscore-prefixed params to avoid lint noise. Satisfies the abstract contract from [FormComponentEventBaseConsumer](file:///Users/shilo/Work/Projects/redbox/redbox-portal/feature/typeahead-onitemselect/angular/projects/researchdatabox/form/src/app/form-state/events/form-component-base-event-consumer.ts#36-316) but is never called; all consumption goes through `handleItemSelected()`.

**`handleItemSelected(event)`** â€” new protected method with the actual consumption logic:
- Cast event to `FieldItemSelectedEvent`.
- If `selectedItem` is null â†’ `control.setValue(onItemSelect.clearValue ?? null, {emitEvent: false})`.
- Otherwise: resolve via `lodash.get(selectedItem.raw, rawPath)`, falling back to `lodash.get(selectedItem, rawPath)` when `raw` is undefined. If **both** resolve to `undefined` â†’ use `clearValue ?? null` (treats unresolvable path the same as a cleared selection).
- `control.setValue(resolved, {emitEvent: false})` â€” prevents cascading change events.

